To keep a clan going there must be a certain level of activity.  The
requirements to remain active are reduced for gangs (Gangs are clans that have
not established a type).  A clan that does not have enough activity is subject
to deactivation.

A gang is considered active if:
At least 200 tribute points are donated per week.

A clan is considered active if:
At least 500 tribute points are donated per week.

{YInactivity is not implemented yet.{x

If a clan is inactive for two weeks, their type will be removed and their hall
entry will be unlinked with no refund provided.  Clan members that had logged
out in the hall will log on at the altar respawn.  To reactivate, a leader
needs to declare a type and link the hall back into the world.  This will
require an initiation, because the clan previously had a type.

If a gang is inactive for two weeks, their status will be downgraded to
inactive and all members will be marked accordingly.  Their name will become
available to anyone who wants to establish a clan.  If it was a downgraded
clan, their hall will be entirely removed and they will have the costs refunded
at the standard rates.  To reactivate, a leader must use the establish command
(Because their name may have changed) and initiation must be completed.

All stored tribute, planned objects, and the member list for the clan is
preserved during this process, even if the clan becomes deactivated.

Note if a clan completely deactivates, it will require two sets of initiation
