Clan leaders have responsibility not only for guiding their clans, but their
actions have added weight.

Leader abilities:
guild <character> <rank>: Invite someone to join your clan, with a starting
  rank of <rank>.  It costs 1,000 tribute to guild an outcast.

guild <character> <rank> offline: The same as invite, but it will invite a
  player who is not currently online.  Note that this does not verify the name
  of an offline player, so if you do not get the name exactly right the cost
  will be wasted.  Offline invitations expire after a week if they are not
  accepted.

rank <character>: Sets the character's rank to the desired value.  You may not
  lower another leader's rank.

sanction <character>: Applies sanctions to the target.  You may not sanction
  another leader.  See 'help sanction' for details.

outcast <character>: Kicks someone out of the clan.  You may not outcast
  another leader.

alliance <clan> <duration> <payment> <bribe>: Offer to ally with target clan
  for duration days.  Payment is who will be paying for this alliance, see
  'help alliance' for details on duration, costs and options.

Hall Building: Leaders may edit their halls.  See 'help hall building' for
  details.

{YPlease note that tribute risks and rewards are not implemented yet.{x
Tribute Risks and Rewards:
Clan leaders gain some special bonuses involving tribute, for normal gains and
for pk risks.

Whenever a leader gains merit for a kill, 5% bonus is added to the clan's
tribute storage immediately.  This applies to both straight kills and kill
offerings.  It does not apply to tribute transferred from a slain enemy.

When a leader dies in pk, their clan loses 5 tribute points and the killers
split those points based on looting rules.  If an enemy leader is involved, any
points they steal are multiplied by 5.  So if a leader dies to two enemies, one
that is a leader and one that isn't, and the enemy leader could loot 2 items
then they steal 2 * 5 = 10 points, and the other enemy steals 3, causing a
total value of 13 tribute points to be lost for that leader's death.  This loss
does come straight from the clan's stored tribute, though it can not drive it
negative (Less points would be stolen in that case).

Also see:
help tribute
help loot limit
