Syntax: outcast <player>

To outcast yourself, simply enter the command with no argument.

A leader may outcast a member of their clan by entering the victim's name after
the command.  If someone is outcast by their leader, they have an opportunity
to launch or join a rebellion against that clan for up to a week after being
outcast.  See 'help rebel' for details on rebellions.

Outcasts are cursed by the gods, and will find it much more difficult to make
their way in the world.  Fortunately, they can redeem themselves and move back
to being loners or directly into a new clan.

To move from outcast to loner has two options:
1) You earn 5 times your donation points of merit and commit it. Outcasts may
not dedicate merit, so this must be earned without dying to another player.
2) A clan may pay 10 times your donation points of tribute to have you join
directly.

An outcast may participate in a clan initiation, but the clan will have to earn
extra tribute equal to cost 2) per outcast involved in order to successfully
form.

If an outcast becomes a loner or joins an existing clan, they can no longer
rebel against the clan that outcast them, even if it is within a week.
