0 HEDIT~
None~
0 1 none
syntax: hedit <options>

hedit is short for "hall edit", and is where you access everything related to
hall building.  While editing your hall, you will see the labels for every
object that has been placed in it.

For a quick start example, please see 'help hedit example'

There are three types of objects: Planned, Previewed, and Placed.  When you
edit an object before previewing it, that is a planned object.  When you
preview it, that object becomes previewed.  Then you may place it.  Once it is
previewed, it costs its tribute.  However, removing it restores full tribute.
When you remove a previewed object, it becomes planned again.  You may not
remove a placed object.

{RNote{x: You are responsible for knowing when you will be charged for an action.
  Full details are provided in hedit costs, please review it thoroughly before
  doing work as you will not be refunded for accidental charges.

Here are the commands you may access with hedit:

GENERAL COMMANDS:
hedit - Enter edit mode.  This displays the labels for each object in your
  hall.
hedit check - Tells you if you're in a legal room to place your hall from.
hedit list <type> <planned|placed|all> - List all objects by your filter.
hedit create <type> <label> - Create a planned object with label <label>.  This
  command places you into edit mode.
hedit display <label> - Display the details for an object.  If you are editing
  an object you may leave <label> blank and it will display the currently
  edited object's details.
hedit clone <original> <label> - Create a planned object with label <label>
  that is an exact copy of object with label original.  The original object may
  be planned or placed.
hedit edit <label> - Edit a planned object with label name.  This command
  places you into edit mode.
hedit upgrade <label> <attribute> - Upgrade a placed object in the hall.  Leave
  attribute blank to see current upgradable stats.
hedit delete <label> - Delete an object.  Use this if you are running out of
  allowed objects and want to open some room.  You must be editing an object
  in order to delete it.
hedit swap <old> <new> - Swap a placed or previewed object with a planned
  object.  There will eventually be a fee for this, currently it only swaps
  the text (Name, short, long, description) of the object.  Note that if you
  swap a pit its contents will be dumped on the ground.
hedit rules <start|save|cancel> - Begin editing the rules for your clan.  When
  done, use save to end editing and save the changes or cancel to revert to
  what they were when you started.  Note if you hedit stop or quit the game it
  will automatically save.
hedit charter <start|save|cancel> - Begin editing the charter for your clan.
  When done, use save to end editing and save the changes or cancel to revert
  to what they were when you started.  Note if you hedit stop or quit the game
  it will automatically save.
hedit stop - Exit edit mode and save all changes.  Note: There is no exit
  without saving, all edits are done live.

ITEM/MOB COMMANDS:
hedit preview <label> - Preview a planned mob or item in the room you're in.
hedit place <label> - Place a previewed mob or item in the room you're in.
hedit remove <label> - Remove a placed mob or item in the room you're in.

ROOM COMMANDS: See 'help hedit room' for a detailed list
hedit preview <label> <direction> - Preview a room linked to the room you're in.
hedit place <label> <direction> - Place a previewed room you're in.
