0 1 none
You have some tribute, you're the clan leader, and you want to start your hall.
Here's some examples (Note that examples will often fill in text for you to
replace as appropriate.  If it has <> it's optional text, if it has () around
it it is a note to you and not part of the command at all):

To begin:
hedit

To begin your first room:
hedit create room <entryhall>
hedit name My clan's entry hall
hedit desc + I am writing my entry hall description as if it were a note.
text > The text shortcut automatically puts text into the description too.
text - I didn't like that last line so I want this one instead.
text ++ All the normal note rules apply.
hedit check (See if I'm in a room I can place my first room)
hedit preview <entryhall (Or room_1 if default first room name)> south

Your first room will form to the south, if it's a legal room and you have
enough tribute available.  Before placing, you can also set up the room's
other attributes by other hedit commands, check the help file 'hedit edit' for
a list of your options.

You can repeat this process for other rooms, items, and mobs.  The difference
for items is that a type is required, and both items and mobs need different
fields filled in.  Note that all fields may be filled in in almost any order.
Only fields requiring a previous one (Such as setting liquid requires the item
type to be set to fountain) can't be done at any time.

Please note the included punctuation on the examples -- in general you should
only include punctuation at the end for the in-room description.

Here is a mob:
hedit create mob <healer>
hedit name mighty healer (Keywords to target it)
hedit short A mighty healer (The short name when people interact with this mob)
hedit long A mighty healer stands here, ready to assist you. (In-room desc)
text + A mighty healer stands before you, looking calmly ahead of himself. He
text > does not seem to care who you are, as long as you are a member of his
text > clan he'll help you out. (text can be used without hedit desc to begin)
(Note that text just set the 'look healer' description)
hedit level 51 (Raises his cost, can be set after placing via hedit upgrade)
hedit preview <healer (Or mob_1, etc.)>

Here is an item:
hedit create item <milkfountain>
hedit name cow milk (Keywords to target it)
hedit short a cow (The short name used when people interact with this item)
hedit long A cow stands here, offering you milk. (The in-room description)
hedit type fountain
hedit liquid milk
hedit preview <milkfountain (Or item_1, etc.)>

Finally, you can do two things to a previewed object: You can place it (Which
locks it in) or you can remove it, fully refunding the tribute it cost.  If
your clan has multiple leaders, the leader that previews an item is not able to
place it -- ensuring at least two of three possible leaders approve of that
tribute being spent.  You may not remove the first room you have placed for
your hall, a method to update its text will be added in the future to allow for
corrections in typos or errors made since it has to be locked in (Previewed but
can't be removed like normal) without getting to see it.

To remove a room, you need to be in an adjacent room and enter its label and
direction: hedit remove <room label> <direction>.  To remove an item or mob,
you just need to be in the room it spawns in and hedit remove <label>.

Also see:
help hall building
help hedit
help clan
