Syntax: link <item>
Syntax: unlink <item>

By using a spirit focus, you may link or unlink an item so that enemies may
not take it from you.  Linking and unlinking does not consume the focus, but it
is required that you hold the focus in order to link or unlink gear.  You may
link up to 5 items of your choice.  Being magical in nature, the focus may be
purchased from the magic shop.

{WNote{X: It does not consume the spirit focus to link an item.

When you die to an enemy player, any items linked to you will come with you.
The strain of this transportation will damage the items, with higher quality
items suffering higher damage than lower quality ones.

The following item types may be linked:
Weapons
Armor
Clothing
Jewelry
Drink Containers
Lights
Floats
Containers (Will dump contents into the corpse if you die)

The general rule is that if an item can be permanently destroyed or is a gem
then it can not be linked.

The damage an item suffers is based on its quality.  Item quality definitions
are listed in help search.

Damage amounts:
Stock/Common: 10% damage
Uncommon:     35% damage
Rare:         50% damage
Immload:      Shattered

Unlinking an item deals 1/3rd of the damage that death does.

As long as the item is not already Broken, it will become Broken first.  If a
Broken item receives damage again, it will become Shattered.  In this state it
will cost significantly more to repair.  There is no further damage to items
that have been Shattered.

