Syntax: search <corpse> <option>

Search in a player corpse to see all items.  This will show items in containers
since they are looted directly.  By default, search <corpse> will show items of
uncommon or rare types.  Gems will be marked separately from normal items.  The
lore skill will help with accuracy if you are doing specific searches.

Types:
Stock: A basic item with no modifications.
Common: A lightly enchanted weapon (Through 6/6), piece of armor (Through -3)
Uncommon: A more heavily enchanted weapon (Through 12/12), piece of armor
  (Through -9), or weapon with one extra permanent flag (Holy, vorpal, nether,
  sharp, vampiric -- that the weapon does not start with).  Certain rare spawn
  items also count as uncommon, see the list below.
Rare: A very heavily enchanted weapon (Above 12/12), piece of armor (Above -9),
  weapons with more than one extra permanent flag, or legendary weapons.
  Certain very rare spawn items count as rare, see the list below.
Gem: A gem item type, these do not count against loot limits.  They will list
  in a default search or by searching 'gem'.

Uncommon items: belt of seaweed, flame shroud, kaethan boots, any spell page
  not listed as rare.
Rare items: fire amulet, fractal crystal shard, phoenix feather, krae'tan
  sandals

You may also 'search <corpse> all' to show all types of items.

If <option> is blank, a search for uncommon, rare, and gem is done.  Searching
