0 'LOOT LIMIT'~
None~
0 1 none
When a clanner dies, enemies may loot their corpse.  Up to 5 items may be
looted from a death, and if within 3 ticks not all items that can be looted
have been then all of them return to the victim.

Not everyone may loot an enemy's corpse.  Here is how it is assigned:
The player that lands the killing blow receives 1 item.
The player that deals the most damage (Maladictions have a damage value)
  receives 1 item.
The remaining 3 items are available to anyone who contributed, first come first
  serve.

Gems and coins do not count as part of the loot limit.

If a player dies to an NPC without their pkill timer active, up to 3 items may
be looted by anyone (The killing blow and highest damage items are not
available).  The remaining items will never return if it was an NPC kill.

A clanmate may not loot your corpse unless it was an NPC kill, as that exposes
you to risk of losing more items if they die or are stolen from.

Corpses will not rot as long as you are logged on.
~
0 OFFER 'KILL OFFERING'~
None~
0 1 none
Syntax: offer <corpse>

When you kill another player, you may give up the option to loot and instead
offer your kill to the gods for extra tribute.  If you have looted anything
other than coins from the corpse, you may not make this offering.  To offer a
kill, you must have at least one item available to loot from the corpse.

The kill offering is worth the same amount of tribute as the base kill, so if
you land the kill then offer it you will receive double the normal amount. (The
tribute you take from the victim is separate and is not modified by this).  If
you have not searched the corpse, the bonus merit will go directly into your
clan's tribute.  If you have searched the corpse your offering is tainted and
the bonus will go into your merit instead of directly into your clan's tribute.

If a corpse has had all lootable items already taken, you may not offer it even
if you had items available to loot.

Also see:
help tribute
~
